article.headline: Dartmouth 68, Hartford 56
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Robby Pride scored 19 points as Dartmouth defeated Hartford 68-56 on Saturday night. David Rufful added 15 points, six rebounds and four steals for the Big Green (1-4), while Clive Weeden finished with 12 points and eight rebounds. After leading 27-21 at halftime, Dartmouth went on a 9-0 run early in the second half. Rufful's 3-pointer made the score 36-23 with 16:38 remaining. The Big Green took their largest lead of the night after a free throw from Pride with 1:54 left made the score 58-40. The Hawks (2-4) were led by Morgan Sabia who finished with 13 points and seven assists. Milton Burton added 11 points, while Andres Torres chipped in with 10 points. Dartmouth shot 44.7 percent from the field (21-for-47). The Hawks shot only 36.5 percent (23-for-63), and shot 50 percent from the free throw line (4-for-8).
